    "A large width implies that activation and silence are almost equally likely for recurrent input near threshold.",
    "A small width implies that activation is almost guaranteed for recurrent input above threshold and almost impossible for input below threshold.",
    "See Methods for the full expression of this update rule.",
    "The threshold θ represents the general inhibitory tone of CA3 and plays a key role in retrieval.",
    "At high θ, neural activity is disfavored, so we expect the network to retrieve the sparser, more strongly stored MF encoding of the cue."
